  questionText: Why is ethanol heated in a water bath?
  referenceImage: {fileID: 0}
  explanationText: When bumping occurs, the vapours released can come in contact
    with fire and ignite. This can cause accidents.
  options:
  - Flammable liquids can catch fire if bumping occurs
  - Ethanol heats faster in a water bath
  - Ethanol evaporates and condenses in a water bath set up
  - None of the above
